headline: Assessing Huntington Ingalls Industries (HII) Valuation After Key Defense Wins And USS Zumwalt Milestone
summary: Huntington Ingalls Industries (HII) is back in focus after Ingalls Shipbuilding completed builder’s sea trials for the modernized USS Zumwalt and Mission Technologies secured a role on the 10 year, $25.4b ATSP5 contract. See our latest analysis for Huntington Ingalls Industries. Those contract wins and shipbuilding milestones come as the share price trades at $424.14, with a 30 day share price return of 19.64% and a 1 year total shareholder return of 112.63%.
